-- [RI] Sources are the official RI General Assembly statute server (webserver.rilegislature.gov). RESIDENTIAL = ch. 34-18 (URLTA-based), governing standard dwelling units (apartments, single-family).
-- [RI] OMITTED provisions (statute specifies no value — did not invent):
-- [RI] - late_fee_max_pct: Ch. 34-18 imposes no cap on late fees. No section caps or sets a percentage; late fees are unregulated as to amount.
-- [RI] - late_fee_grace_days: Ch. 34-18 has no grace period before a late fee may be charged. The 15-day figure in § 34-18-35 ("If any part of the stipulated rent is due and in arrears for fifteen (15) days, the landlord shall send a written notice") is the threshold for an EVICTION-FOR-NONPAYMENT demand notice, NOT a late-fee grace period — so it is not encoded as late_fee_grace_days.
-- [RI] UNIT-TYPE COVERAGE notes:
-- [RI] - rv_spot: No dedicated long-term RV-tenancy act in RI. RV parks/campgrounds are regulated under Title 32, ch. 32-7 (health/safety/licensing of RV parks and campgrounds), which is NOT a landlord-tenant tenancy statute. Long-term RV occupants may be tenants under general law, but no statute squarely assigns RV-spot tenancies to 34-18 or 31-44, so rv_spot is not asserted under any act here.
-- [RI] - storage: No self-storage / self-service-storage-facility lien act surfaced within the landlord-tenant titles searched; not represented.
-- [RI] - mobile_home: ch. 31-44 (Title 31) governs mobile/manufactured home park tenancies (separate from 34-18) — includes §§ 31-44-2 evictions/termination, 31-44-7 lease, 31-44-7.1 security deposits.
-- [RI] ENTRY notice: statute states "two (2) days" — converted to 48 hours for the hours-based schema field.
