-- [MT] Official source: Montana Code Annotated on the Montana Legislature site. Note the legacy host leg.mt.gov 301-redirects to archive.legmt.gov and then to the canonical mca.legmt.gov; all URLs above use the canonical host.
-- [MT] ACTS:
-- [MT] - Residential (Ch. 24): governs dwelling units — apartments and single-family. Long-term RV occupancy for residential dwelling purposes (30+ consecutive days) falls under residential/mobile-home framework rather than a separate act; short-term/transient RV-park and campground stays (<30 days) are EXCLUDED from Ch. 24 per 70-24-104 / SB251 (2017). Mapped rv_spot to both Ch. 24 and Ch. 33 to reflect this; there is no standalone RV act.
-- [MT] - Mobile Home (Ch. 33): Montana Residential Mobile Home Lot Rental Act — lot/space rental to owners of mobile/manufactured homes; also covers long-term RV space rentals used as residential dwellings. 90-day termination notice for legitimate business reasons; 6-month notice on change of park use.
-- [MT] - Storage (Ch. 6 Part 6): Self-Storage Facilities Act — operator's lien, 60-day default before lien sale.
-- [MT] - Commercial (Ch. 26): Montana has NO comprehensive dedicated commercial-tenancy act. Ch. 26 ("Landlord and Tenant — Residential and Commercial") is a thin set of general lease provisions (assignment, attornment, change of lease terms by notice at 70-26-109, etc.) applying to both residential and commercial; commercial tenancies are otherwise governed by the parties' contract and common law.
-- [MT] RESIDENTIAL PROVISIONS — included:
-- [MT] - entry_notice_hours = 24 (70-24-312).
-- [MT] - deposit_return_days = 30 (70-25-202). Security deposits are governed by a SEPARATE chapter (Ch. 25, Residential Tenants' Security Deposits), cross-referenced by Ch. 24 at 70-24-112. The 30-day outer deadline applies when there are any deductions (the landlord must furnish a written list of damages/charges and refund the balance within 30 days); a shorter 10-day deadline applies ONLY when there are zero damages, no cleaning, no unpaid rent, and no unpaid utilities ('the landlord shall return the security deposit within 10 days', 70-25-202). Recorded 30 as the general statutory max.
-- [MT] - notice_to_vacate_days = 30 (70-24-441).
-- [MT] RESIDENTIAL PROVISIONS — OMITTED (no statutory value exists; not invented):
-- [MT] - deposit_max_months: Montana does NOT cap security deposit amount. Reviewed entire Ch. 25 (70-25-101 through 70-25-206) — no cap-by-months or dollar-cap section exists.
-- [MT] - late_fee_max_pct: Montana does NOT cap late fees. 70-24-201 leaves rent/late-fee terms to the rental agreement ('Rent means all payments... including rent, late fees, or other charges as agreed on in the rental agreement'); no statutory percentage cap.
-- [MT] - late_fee_grace_days: No statutory grace period before a late fee may apply; rent is 'payable without demand or notice at the time and place agreed upon' (70-24-201). Omitted.
